\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Two halves of one puzzle. The healthy atlas (left) carries a quantitative portal$\to $central position but no disease; the single-nucleus cohort (right) spans the whole disease course but has thrown its positions away. The project's one move is to fit the left piece's ruler into the right piece's cells --- using the healthy gradient to assign each diseased nucleus a pseudo-zonation coordinate.\relax }}{11}{figure.caption.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:jigsaw}{{3}{11}{Two halves of one puzzle. The healthy atlas (left) carries a quantitative portal$\to $central position but no disease; the single-nucleus cohort (right) spans the whole disease course but has thrown its positions away. The project's one move is to fit the left piece's ruler into the right piece's cells --- using the healthy gradient to assign each diseased nucleus a pseudo-zonation coordinate.\relax }{figure.caption.8}{}}
